---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '@/components/Navbar';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Layout & Composition - Web Interfaces">
  <Navbar client:idle />
  
  <main class="lg:ml-64 min-h-screen bg-white">
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 pt-20 lg:pt-16 pb-12 lg:pb-16 border-b border-gray-200">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <a href="/" class="inline-block text-sm text-[#9ca3af] hover:text-black transition-colors mb-6 underline">
          Back
        </a>
        <h1 class="main-text text-black mb-4">
          Layout & Composition
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-gray-600">
          Mastering the fundamentals of visual arrangement and spatial design for the web.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold text-black mb-6">The Foundation of Design</h2>
        <p class="text-base lg:text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Layout and composition form the backbone of effective web design. How you arrange elements on a page 
          determines not only aesthetics but also usability, hierarchy, and the overall user experience.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base lg:text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Good composition guides the eye, creates balance, and makes complex information feel simple and organized. 
          This section covers the principles and techniques for creating effective layouts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Core Principles -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold text-black mb-8">Core Principles</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-10">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">1. Grid Systems</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Use grids to create consistency and structure. Grid systems provide a framework for organizing content 
              and maintaining alignment across different screen sizes and layouts.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">2. White Space</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Embrace white space as a design element. Proper spacing improves readability, creates visual breathing room, 
              and helps establish hierarchy between elements.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">3. Visual Balance</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Create equilibrium in your layouts through symmetrical or asymmetrical balance. Consider visual weight, 
              color distribution, and the placement of focal points.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">4. Rhythm & Pattern</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Establish visual rhythm through repetition and variation. Consistent patterns help users predict 
              and understand interface behavior while adding visual interest.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">5. Responsive Composition</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Design layouts that adapt gracefully across devices. Think mobile-first and consider how your composition 
              transforms from small screens to large displays.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black mb-3">6. Focal Points</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Direct attention strategically using size, contrast, and placement. Every page should have a clear 
              focal point that guides users to the most important content or action.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Best Practices -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold text-black mb-8">Best Practices</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Start with Content</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Let content drive layout decisions. Understand what needs to be communicated before deciding how to arrange it.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Use Consistent Spacing</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Establish a spacing scale (4px, 8px, 16px, 32px, etc.) and use it consistently throughout your designs.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Align Elements</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Proper alignment creates order and professionalism. Use guides and grids to ensure elements line up correctly.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black mb-2">Test at Multiple Sizes</h4>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Always preview layouts on different devices and screen sizes. What works on desktop may break on mobile.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Main text - responsive sizing */
  .main-text {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 32px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .main-text {
      font-size: 42px;
      line-height: 50px;
    }
  }
</style>